## 4. Design System Enforcement

**Before writing or modifying ANY UI code**, you MUST follow these rules:

### The Three Laws of Color
1. **Teal for actions** â€” every CTA, toggle, active state, tier badge, interactive highlight
2. **Blue for data** â€” clicks, sessions, impressions, info badges, progress bars (read-only, never actionable)
3. **Purple for admin AI only** â€” `AdminChat.tsx` and `SeoAudit.tsx` "Flag for Client". **Never in client-facing views.**

### Color Decision Quick Reference
```
Button / CTA / toggle?      â†’ Teal (from-teal-600 to-emerald-600)
Data metric?                 â†’ Blue (text-blue-400, bg-blue-500/10)
Admin AI feature?            â†’ Purple (purple-400/purple-600)
Score (health/perf)?         â†’ scoreColor() from constants.ts
Status badge?                â†’ green (success), amber (warning), red (error), orange (changes requested), blue (info/review), teal (client requested)
Tier badge (client)?         â†’ Teal (all tiers) or zinc (free)
```

### Forbidden
- **Never** use `violet`, `indigo`, or introduce new hue families without explicit user approval
- **Never** hand-roll card markup â€” use `<SectionCard>`
- **Never** hand-roll stat displays â€” use `<StatCard>` or `<CompactStatBar>`
- **Never** hard-code score colors â€” use `scoreColor()` / `scoreColorClass()` from `ui/constants.ts`
- **Never** use purple in any client-facing component

